WEBVTT

00:06.005 --> 00:09.718
♪ Amazing grace ♪

00:10.385 --> 00:13.888
♪ How sweet the sound ♪

00:14.764 --> 00:20.729
♪ That saved a wretch like me ♪

00:23.273 --> 00:27.068
♪ I once was lost ♪

00:27.569 --> 00:31.156
♪ But now am found ♪

00:31.823 --> 00:37.662
♪ Was blind, but now I see ♪

00:43.126 --> 00:46.004
We are on our way to Gay, Georgia.

00:46.087 --> 00:48.214
-G-A-Y
-[Bobby] It's literally called

00:48.298 --> 00:49.758
-Gay, Georgia.
-[Karamo chuckles]

00:49.841 --> 00:52.677
I looked up Gay,
and the population is 89 people.

00:52.761 --> 00:54.429
-That's big.
-And their big--

00:54.637 --> 00:55.472
Big?

00:55.555 --> 00:57.891
I used to live in a town
that had nine.

00:57.974 --> 01:01.436
-Love it.
-We actually have a special treat, guys.

01:01.519 --> 01:03.980
-We're doing a lady.
-Yes!

01:04.064 --> 01:05.857
I haven't done a lady in years.

01:05.940 --> 01:09.110
-We've never done a lady.
-I have never done a lady.

01:09.360 --> 01:10.779
Oh, I just got the joke.

01:10.862 --> 01:13.573
-Our lady this week--
-You're homos. I got it.

01:14.115 --> 01:17.911
[Widelife's "All Things
(Just Keep Getting Better)" playing]

01:21.790 --> 01:24.459
♪ You came into my life ♪

01:24.542 --> 01:28.129
♪ And my world never looked so bright ♪

01:28.588 --> 01:31.716
♪ It's true
You bring out the best in me ♪

01:31.800 --> 01:35.345
♪ When you are around ♪

01:39.182 --> 01:40.850
♪ Things keep getting better ♪

01:46.397 --> 01:48.191
♪ Things keep getting better ♪

01:53.530 --> 01:55.198
♪ Things keep getting better ♪

02:03.998 --> 02:06.251
Our lady this week, Tammye.

02:06.334 --> 02:10.004
She's 5'1" and... [squeaks] pounds
'cause you don't tell a lady's weight.

02:10.088 --> 02:11.422
-All right.
-Correct.

02:11.506 --> 02:12.715
[laughs] That's me.

02:13.758 --> 02:15.343
She is nominated by Gene,

02:15.426 --> 02:17.387
-her friend and neighbor.
-Cute.

02:17.470 --> 02:21.266
If the world was full of Tammyes,
we wouldn't have problems.

02:21.349 --> 02:23.768
[Tammye]
God has given me a precious gift.

02:23.852 --> 02:28.148
I'm on this planet not for myself,
but for the betterment of humanity.

02:28.231 --> 02:30.775
She is sweet. She's loving. She's caring.

02:31.359 --> 02:34.988
She's actually more sweet, loving, caring
for others than she is for herself.

02:35.071 --> 02:36.614
Miss Tammye's a very busy woman.

02:36.698 --> 02:38.783
[Tammye] I have three children
and a husband.

02:38.867 --> 02:40.785
-How's school going?
-It's good.

02:40.869 --> 02:42.036
[Gene] She loves church.

02:42.120 --> 02:44.455
[Tammye] I hug every person
that walks into church.

02:44.539 --> 02:46.749
She's a teacher
over in Coweta County.

02:46.833 --> 02:50.044
I also do Hospital Homebound
for children who are sick.

02:50.128 --> 02:53.798
I visit them after school,
and then I make my own way home,

02:53.882 --> 02:57.719
and grade papers,
and I try to fix something quick to eat.

02:57.802 --> 03:00.597
Something fast,
a fast meal that's fast to cook.

03:01.264 --> 03:02.515
[man] Do you eat fast food?

03:04.475 --> 03:06.686
I eat fast foods. [chuckles]

03:07.020 --> 03:10.690
Instead of getting help with her home,
Tammye hopes the Fab 5 will help

03:10.773 --> 03:13.026
-with the community center.
-All right.

03:13.109 --> 03:17.155
This weekend, Tammye's church is throwing
their annual Homecoming Service.

03:17.238 --> 03:19.324
-Do y'all know what that is?
-I do.

03:19.407 --> 03:22.410
[Gene] Each year, most local country
churches have the homecoming,

03:22.493 --> 03:27.206
and they're asking the ones that haven't
been in a while to come and socialize,

03:27.290 --> 03:30.001
and get encouraged
to start attending again.

03:30.084 --> 03:32.420
Her passion for the community
runs in her family.

03:32.545 --> 03:35.465
Aw, Tammye's grandmother
was a sharecropper,

03:35.548 --> 03:39.677
and she co-founded this church
at her kitchen table over 50 years ago.

03:39.761 --> 03:42.222
Back when "gay" just meant happy.

03:42.972 --> 03:45.725
Miss Tammye, uh,
was diagnosed with cancer.

03:46.559 --> 03:49.062
Then her sister and her mother
all at the same time.

03:49.145 --> 03:51.731
And her mother unfortunately
didn't survive.

03:53.149 --> 03:55.151
[Tammye] This is the first homecoming--

03:56.736 --> 03:57.612
Excuse me.

03:58.238 --> 03:59.280
--without my mom.

04:00.198 --> 04:03.243
So, that's gonna be bittersweet.

04:04.577 --> 04:09.207
Tammye's son, Myles, he's 22,
and he just moved back home from Atlanta.

04:09.290 --> 04:12.085
He does not feel comfortable
going back to their church,

04:12.168 --> 04:15.255
because he doesn't feel welcome anymore
after coming out as gay.

04:15.338 --> 04:17.257
Or even the homecoming, for that matter.

04:17.340 --> 04:19.759
The Church is what I feel alienated by,
not God.

04:19.842 --> 04:22.053
I feel loved and accepted
by God and Jesus.

04:22.136 --> 04:25.723
It's the politics of the Church
is what made me feel not welcome.

04:25.807 --> 04:30.061
That was people saying, "I love you.
I just don't accept your lifestyle."

04:30.144 --> 04:31.646
[Bobby] I can relate to that.

04:31.729 --> 04:35.275
Not everyone in the Church is that way.
And not all churches are that way.

04:35.358 --> 04:38.528
I love the Church, and I have loved
every experience.

04:38.611 --> 04:40.446
I have always used my strength

04:40.530 --> 04:43.366
to encourage them
to see in a different light.

04:43.449 --> 04:46.202
-That's beautiful.
-Let's be open-minded.

04:46.286 --> 04:50.707
So, our mission this week is to help
Tammye go from hot mess to Sunday best.

04:50.790 --> 04:52.125
[all] Yeah!

04:52.208 --> 04:54.127
[rock music playing]

04:59.841 --> 05:03.052
That's his truck. That looks
like a truck Gene would drive.

05:03.136 --> 05:04.762
That is a bright red truck.

05:04.846 --> 05:06.014
[Bobby] Let's find Gene.

05:07.515 --> 05:09.225
-Come on.
-Got it.

05:09.309 --> 05:13.438
"Notice: No firearms--" Really?
They gotta put a sign saying "no guns"?

05:14.188 --> 05:16.733
-Gene?
-Oh, my God, he looks like my dad.

05:16.816 --> 05:18.818
-Nice to meet you.
-Hey, I'm Bobby.

05:18.901 --> 05:20.653
It's a pleasure to meet you.

05:20.737 --> 05:23.698
-You have awesome boots.
-[Tan] That's a crisp hat, too.

05:23.781 --> 05:25.950
-You're a snazzy dresser.
-[Gene] Thank you.

05:26.034 --> 05:28.870
-So, why nominate Tammye?
-Tammye's a sweet lady.

05:28.953 --> 05:33.124
Been through a lot in the last year,
so it's been a rough ride for her.

05:33.207 --> 05:35.585
You're helping with the community space?

05:35.668 --> 05:40.048
Yeah, we started this last year,
but they only had so much funds available.

05:40.131 --> 05:44.635
So, um, we got it up and dried in,
and, uh, it's been sitting here.

05:44.719 --> 05:48.139
This was a vision of theirs years ago,
was to have this community center.

05:48.222 --> 05:51.184
What are they planning
on using this building for?

05:51.267 --> 05:52.310
I think their goal

05:52.393 --> 05:55.772
is to have it to where they can
have one, two days a week

05:55.897 --> 05:58.816
where elderly people--
Even not members of the church.

05:58.900 --> 06:02.820
But they can come here and maybe
have a meal, socialize and visit.

06:03.196 --> 06:04.530
-Nice.
-I love that.

06:04.614 --> 06:07.241
I think they're hoping
to maybe start a day care here.

06:07.325 --> 06:09.994
-Oh, nice.
-[Gene] Some of the young ladies here

06:10.078 --> 06:13.039
and single moms that are struggling
that can't afford day care.

06:13.122 --> 06:15.416
-Maybe they can start a program in here.
-Nice.

06:15.500 --> 06:18.086
-We could have bingo, too, I don't know.
-[laughing]

06:18.169 --> 06:20.671
-Can you take us to Tammye?
-Be glad to.

06:20.755 --> 06:22.673
-Yes!
-Let's get out of here.

06:22.757 --> 06:25.510
-Come on.
-Wanna take a look inside the church?

06:25.593 --> 06:26.552
[Jonathan] Yeah.

06:27.053 --> 06:27.887
Thank you.

06:28.012 --> 06:29.388
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

06:30.765 --> 06:31.933
-I'm good.
-You're good.

06:32.016 --> 06:33.851
-Wow, so much red.
-[Gene] Go ahead.

06:34.519 --> 06:36.229
-You all right? Wanna stay?
-Mm-hm.

06:36.312 --> 06:37.939
-You sure?
-[Antoni] Is that a tree?

06:38.314 --> 06:40.441
-It's so--
-[Karamo singing]

06:41.025 --> 06:43.778
Y'all gonna do all the singing,
I'm gonna do the preaching.

06:43.861 --> 06:47.156
-It's beautiful. It's cute.
-[Gene] It's been here a long time.

06:47.240 --> 06:50.243
In my experience with religion
and religious people,

06:50.326 --> 06:51.452
I've just been judged.

06:51.536 --> 06:54.122
You look like the gay that's scared
they're gonna burn

06:54.205 --> 06:56.374
-[laughs]
-when they cross the door.

06:56.582 --> 07:00.378
-Okay. Can I ride with you, Gene? Yeah.
-Sure. Who wants to ride with me?

07:00.461 --> 07:01.921
-Wanna ride with us, too?
-Sure.

07:02.004 --> 07:04.340
[Bobby] I don't like being involved
with the Church,

07:04.423 --> 07:07.301
because there's so much hate
against gays

07:07.385 --> 07:10.012
and fights against our just basic rights

07:10.096 --> 07:13.224
that I have a hard time
making peace with it.

07:16.018 --> 07:17.979
[Tan] Do you have Muslims in this town?

07:18.062 --> 07:20.982
-I'm assuming not many in Gay.
-Where does he or she live?

07:21.065 --> 07:21.899
Yeah.

07:21.983 --> 07:25.153
I'm pretty sure we're thin
on gays and Muslims.

07:25.236 --> 07:26.070
Okay.

07:27.363 --> 07:30.408
Picture it. Click on Netflix
and turn on that Bob Ross collection

07:30.491 --> 07:31.868
they have on there now.

07:31.951 --> 07:32.952
So peaceful.

07:33.035 --> 07:35.913
You're taking a little gander.
You see a little side street.

07:35.997 --> 07:38.791
Let me go down there.
You come upon a little horse farm.

07:38.875 --> 07:43.045
See little birds living up there,
and some hay over there.

07:43.129 --> 07:45.047
That's Tammye's house. Gorgeous.

07:45.131 --> 07:47.049
[Tan] Had a nice drive?
Isn't it beautiful?

07:47.133 --> 07:49.010
[Bobby] Yeah. Reminds me of home.

07:49.093 --> 07:52.513
Oh, I love a good front porch
with rocking chairs.

07:54.140 --> 07:55.183
[Gene] Miss Tammye.

07:56.267 --> 07:57.393
Miss Tammye, you here?

07:57.477 --> 07:58.352
-Hey.
-Hey.

07:58.436 --> 08:01.439
-Hi, good-looking. How're you doing?
-Come here. Let me see you.

08:01.522 --> 08:02.815
[all] Hi.

08:02.899 --> 08:06.444
-Oh, my God.
-I wanna introduce you to the Fabulous 5.

08:06.527 --> 08:08.738
-Oh, my God.
-[Gene] This is Miss Tammye.

08:08.821 --> 08:10.948
-You guys are fabulous.
-How are you?

08:11.032 --> 08:13.618
This is one sweet lady.
You'll never meet one finer.

08:13.701 --> 08:16.120
-Hey, it's been great.
-Thanks, Gene.

08:16.204 --> 08:19.415
-Mm, I smell something frying.
-You better come in here.

08:19.499 --> 08:22.793
I'm walking slowly.
I can't contain my excitement.

08:22.877 --> 08:25.755
[Tammye] Can't live in Georgia
without fried green tomatoes.

08:25.838 --> 08:27.924
-Come on, y'all try one.
-[Tan] Thank you.

08:28.007 --> 08:29.967
-Mm. Those are good.
-[Tammye] Sinful.

08:30.051 --> 08:31.219
This is sinful.

08:31.677 --> 08:34.263
Ooh, wow.
Do we call you Miss Tammye or Tammye?

08:34.347 --> 08:35.223
Call me Mama.

08:35.306 --> 08:36.474
-[Tan] Mama.
-Oh, yeah.

08:36.557 --> 08:37.517
Mama Tammye.

08:37.600 --> 08:39.227
-Yeah.
-I'll be Mama Tammye.

08:39.310 --> 08:42.063
-I love that.
-I'm your mom away from home.

08:42.146 --> 08:43.439
-I love that.
-Yeah.

08:43.523 --> 08:46.442
I'm so far away from my mom,
so I will take that.

08:46.526 --> 08:48.736
We just saw the community center.

08:48.819 --> 08:51.280
-We saw the church. Amazing.
-Yes.

08:51.364 --> 08:53.950
-You guys raised all that money.
-[Tammye] Bless my heart.

08:54.033 --> 08:57.036
You made this building.
What's on your vision board?

08:57.578 --> 08:58.663
Oh, my vision.

08:58.955 --> 09:02.458
I want it to be a place
that we can feed people

09:02.542 --> 09:04.126
spiritually and naturally,

09:04.210 --> 09:08.631
where everyone that walks in the door
can feel love.

09:08.714 --> 09:10.216
-Yeah!
-All right!

09:10.299 --> 09:13.511
-Yay, guys.
-Can we see the rest of the house?

09:13.761 --> 09:15.263
-Yes, we'd love to.
-Yes.

09:16.472 --> 09:18.891
This is Myles' room. Coming in.

09:19.559 --> 09:20.768
Oh, my gosh.

09:20.851 --> 09:22.853
-[Tammye] Careful. Step over things.
-Myles.

09:22.937 --> 09:24.939
[Tan] I'm assuming Myles is single

09:25.022 --> 09:27.441
-if he's living messily.
-[Tammye] Yes.

09:27.525 --> 09:29.527
-Nobody wants this in their partner.
-No.

09:29.610 --> 09:31.612
[Jonathan] Karamo is so upset, he's like--

09:31.696 --> 09:34.407
-I'm like-- Yes.
-Going crazy on the inside.

09:34.490 --> 09:38.119
There's no way as a parent
that I'm walking in to my door

09:38.202 --> 09:41.414
and see a trail of my child's clothes
and I'm cool with it.

09:41.497 --> 09:43.583
[Tammye]
He says this is his creative mess.

09:43.666 --> 09:45.668
[Bobby] That's a BS excuse.

09:46.252 --> 09:48.379
We'll deal with him.
Can we see your room?

09:48.462 --> 09:49.547
Yes, come on.

09:49.630 --> 09:51.674
Careful. Be careful.

09:51.757 --> 09:53.759
-This is me right here.
-[Tan] Nice and tidy.

09:53.843 --> 09:56.012
-On the whole?
-[Tammye] Can I close this door?

09:56.095 --> 09:57.138
-No.
-No, no.

09:57.221 --> 09:58.139
-No?
-Nope.

09:58.598 --> 10:00.516
[Tan] Oh, my God, what happened?

10:00.600 --> 10:03.978
-Mama, what happened?
-[Tammye] That's my creative mess.

10:04.061 --> 10:07.106
[Bobby] I'm starting to see
where Baby Myles gets it.

10:07.273 --> 10:10.484
If I have a messy room,
it gives me so much anxiety.

10:10.568 --> 10:13.654
This is causing more anxiety
than you need. You're already busy.

10:13.738 --> 10:15.072
This is gonna add to it.

10:15.156 --> 10:16.907
What is it you're wearing to church?

10:16.991 --> 10:21.120
I'm the head usher at church, and usually,
I wear something black,

10:21.203 --> 10:22.955
or a combination of black and white.

10:23.039 --> 10:25.458
It's the uniform color of the ushers.

10:25.541 --> 10:29.086
It's just comfortable,
because I'm there for everybody else.

10:29.170 --> 10:30.630
And I'm never off-duty.

10:30.713 --> 10:31.631
[Tan] Okay. Okay.

10:31.714 --> 10:33.633
-But I love that.
-[Tan] Okay.

10:33.716 --> 10:36.344
There's that amazing hat. Can I grab that?

10:36.427 --> 10:38.179
-Oh, yes.
-That's beautiful.

10:38.262 --> 10:39.805
-Okay.
-Oh, that's Patty's.

10:39.889 --> 10:42.516
-So, who's Miss Patty?
-That was my mom.

10:42.600 --> 10:43.809
Oh, it was?

10:43.893 --> 10:46.771
She was known as the Hat Lady.
She wore her hats to church.

10:46.854 --> 10:49.148
[Tan] Do you wear hats also to church?

10:49.231 --> 10:53.319
No, I don't. You know, I never thought
about it until she passed away,

10:53.402 --> 10:56.364
'cause I always thought--
I had the round face.

10:56.447 --> 10:58.491
I didn't think the hats would work.

10:58.574 --> 11:00.618
Can I see it on? Do you mind?

11:01.369 --> 11:04.914
Her mom nursed Mama Tammye
and her sister back to health

11:05.039 --> 11:06.415
when they had breast cancer.

11:07.124 --> 11:10.670
When she walks in that homecoming,
I want her to feel the spirit of her mom.

11:10.753 --> 11:12.880
Oh, you look beautiful in it.

11:13.714 --> 11:16.467
-It's so cute. It looks real good.
-You guys say I look--

11:16.550 --> 11:18.677
I want her to feel the power
that her mom had,

11:18.761 --> 11:20.638
the command that her mom had of a room.

11:21.305 --> 11:24.642
For everything you do for the community,
you deserve self-care.

11:24.725 --> 11:28.187
-You're gonna make me like a diva?
-Oh, my gosh.

11:28.270 --> 11:30.523
-Oh, diva.
-Mama, you don't even know.

11:30.606 --> 11:32.566
You don't even know.

11:32.650 --> 11:34.610
-[Tammye] Are you serious?
-Yeah.

11:34.693 --> 11:37.738
-[Antoni] Do you grow these tomatoes?
-I do. I grew these.

11:37.822 --> 11:39.448
What's the goal?

11:39.990 --> 11:41.659
-It's homecoming.
-Yeah.

11:41.742 --> 11:44.286
Homecoming is a long-standing tradition.

11:44.370 --> 11:45.454
I love that word.

11:45.538 --> 11:47.665
-Oh, home, come on home, baby.
-Uh-huh.

11:48.165 --> 11:53.254
It's that one day in the year
where everybody comes together.

11:53.337 --> 11:55.339
And you'll have food--

11:55.423 --> 11:59.009
-What are you contributing?
-I usually make macaroni salad.

11:59.093 --> 12:01.137
-Talk me through it.
-Macaroni and eggs,

12:01.220 --> 12:04.515
-some pickles, a little taste of mustard,
-Mm-hm.

12:05.099 --> 12:08.269
-mayonnaise, onion--
-Mm-hm. A lot of mayonnaise?

12:10.187 --> 12:12.481
-Guilty.
-Did you have to ask that?

12:12.565 --> 12:14.275
-Did you have to ask?
-Hey.

12:14.358 --> 12:17.653
I know our goal this week
is to help finish this community center.

12:17.736 --> 12:21.699
But sounds like Tammye has the homecoming
figured out in this potluck situation.

12:21.782 --> 12:26.078
For once, I'm not the one teaching.
I'm here to learn, help and be of service.

12:26.162 --> 12:27.705
I wanna hug you again.

12:27.788 --> 12:30.166
-Anytime, anytime.
-You're a treasure.

12:30.249 --> 12:31.917
Look at your bedroom, honey.

12:32.001 --> 12:35.129
-Let's get up here and have a chat.
-Just roll around.

12:35.212 --> 12:36.964
-Can I take my shoes off?
-Okay.

12:37.047 --> 12:38.757
-Can I take mine off?
-Yes, queen.

12:38.841 --> 12:41.093
-Let me take my shoes off.
-Let's cuddle, chat.

12:41.177 --> 12:43.095
-I'm home.
-I'm living for your short hair.

12:43.179 --> 12:46.140
-Did I tell you why I wear short hair?
-No.

12:46.432 --> 12:48.017
My hair used to be really long.

12:48.100 --> 12:53.355
And then, uh, when I was diagnosed
with cancer, of course, it all fell out.

12:53.439 --> 12:55.065
You know, I was just bald.

12:55.149 --> 12:58.110
And I was about to put on, like, scarves,

12:58.194 --> 12:59.528
-and thought about it.
-Yeah.

12:59.612 --> 13:02.656
And then it was like God spoke to me.
He said, "Don't put it on."

13:02.740 --> 13:07.661
He said, "Take it off. I want people
to see openly what I'm doing for you."

13:07.745 --> 13:08.787
-Take it off.
-Oh.

13:08.871 --> 13:13.000
-And I rocked my bald for a year.
-'Cause your face is gorgeous.

13:13.083 --> 13:16.086
You got cheekbones all over the place.
You got these big eyes.

13:16.253 --> 13:18.797
-Your face is gorgeous.
-Let me ask you something.

13:18.881 --> 13:20.090
What about the gray?

13:20.216 --> 13:24.136
Here's the thing. I'm down with you
coloring your hair to cover the sparkle.

13:24.220 --> 13:26.597
-I feel like the top is too light.
-Yeah.

13:26.680 --> 13:29.767
I wanna blend it together
and create a more natural look.

13:29.850 --> 13:32.186
I can make it so shiny, so pretty.
Oh, my gosh.

13:32.269 --> 13:36.273
We're gonna have a Steel Magnolias moment.
It'll be fun. I love it. You deserve it.

13:36.357 --> 13:38.526
-I love you.
-I love you.

13:39.193 --> 13:40.736
[Jonathan] Hi, boys.

13:41.237 --> 13:43.113
-How are you guys?
-How's it going here?

13:43.197 --> 13:44.448
-Good.
-Hello, Tammye.

13:44.532 --> 13:45.824
[Jonathan] Welcome.

13:46.325 --> 13:49.119
-We just got out of bed.
-We did. We did.

13:49.578 --> 13:52.039
-We were having a full-on cuddle.
-Yes.

13:52.122 --> 13:52.998
[Jonathan] We were.

13:53.082 --> 13:56.335
We kicked our shoes off.
Then get up in this bed.

13:56.418 --> 13:58.254
We can leave them on the stairway.

13:58.337 --> 14:00.464
-Hey.
-Oh, speaking of.

14:00.548 --> 14:02.716
-How are you?
-Hi.

14:03.384 --> 14:05.010
[Tan] Hi, how are you?

14:05.135 --> 14:06.762
I'm Tan. Nice to meet you.

14:06.845 --> 14:09.390
I'm liking your shoes
and your jeans combo.

14:09.473 --> 14:10.766
-No joke.
-[Myles] Thank you.

14:10.849 --> 14:12.935
That fit on those ankles is lovely.

14:13.018 --> 14:15.062
Yes. It's women's size, so--

14:15.145 --> 14:16.689
-Yes!
-[Tan] There you go.

14:16.772 --> 14:18.482
Don't be afraid of lady's wear.

14:18.566 --> 14:20.025
-You just moved back home?
-Yes.

14:20.109 --> 14:23.195
-And she's the major perk of being home?
-[Myles] Oh, yeah.

14:23.279 --> 14:26.240
-Yeah?
-Our relationship's gotten much stronger

14:26.323 --> 14:28.492
-Yeah.
-just by us seeing each other every day.

14:28.576 --> 14:29.410
I can't talk.

14:29.702 --> 14:32.121
Oh, my God, I look at my children.

14:32.204 --> 14:35.875
And for them to respect you,
and to admire you...

14:36.584 --> 14:38.043
-is priceless.
-Yeah.

14:38.127 --> 14:39.253
Definitely a tulip.

14:39.670 --> 14:40.796
[all laughing]

14:40.880 --> 14:41.755
[Tan] Yeah, he is.

14:41.839 --> 14:43.549
Can I spend time with this tulip?

14:43.632 --> 14:44.925
-Is that okay?
-That's fine.

14:45.009 --> 14:46.594
[Karamo] Is that cool? Can we spend time?

14:46.677 --> 14:50.431
I can only imagine growing up
in this town, being black and gay.

14:50.514 --> 14:52.600
Yeah. It's so hard.

14:52.683 --> 14:56.770
I can understand the feelings
of being judged, by experience.

14:56.854 --> 14:59.481
I'm so blessed to have a mother
like I have

15:00.190 --> 15:03.152
'cause mostly, these mothers here,
if you're gay, you're gone.

15:03.235 --> 15:06.405
-There's other gay people down here?
-Like, two. [laughing]

15:06.906 --> 15:09.700
It's just walking down the street,
being called the F-word.

15:09.783 --> 15:11.911
Being called the N-word sometimes.

15:12.912 --> 15:16.916
-And being bullied, like, from the start.
-Yeah.

15:16.999 --> 15:20.544
[Myles] Just because I was different.
I talked and acted differently.

15:20.711 --> 15:25.049
-I just started feeling lonely, you know?
-I see a lot of myself in Myles.

15:25.132 --> 15:29.094
I understand what it was like to grow up
in the South with a loving family.

15:29.178 --> 15:33.933
And then to feel some rejection
from your family, community, your church.

15:34.016 --> 15:35.726
Feeling like, "What do I do now?"

15:35.809 --> 15:40.314
-What do you miss the most about church?
-The music. I see choir as therapy.

15:40.773 --> 15:44.485
And with me, I connect to God with music.

15:45.069 --> 15:48.322
I've really enjoyed meeting you
because I truly see love.

15:48.739 --> 15:51.408
-You know, I grew up really religious.
-Mm-hm.

15:53.827 --> 15:55.454
Yeah? Mm-hm.

15:57.581 --> 16:00.709
There wasn't a day I wasn't at church.
It was my life.

16:00.793 --> 16:03.212
-Those people were my family.
-Mm-hm. Yes.

16:04.088 --> 16:06.840
And I knew from a young age
that I was gay.

16:06.924 --> 16:07.758
Mm-hm.

16:07.841 --> 16:11.345
And I'd be down there at that altar
every Sunday, just crying and begging God

16:11.428 --> 16:13.138
to not make me gay.

16:14.348 --> 16:18.185
Once everyone there found out,
completely turned their back on me.

16:18.310 --> 16:21.355
You know? I wouldn't step foot
in your church today.

16:21.563 --> 16:24.316
-The other guys went in. I wouldn't.
-Wow. Why?

16:24.400 --> 16:27.194
I told myself
I'd never go back to a church.

16:27.903 --> 16:31.949
I was so hurt. And I know
that's what Myles is going through.

16:32.032 --> 16:33.200
Mm-hm.

16:33.409 --> 16:36.787
What was it about being in the big city
that made you say, "I gotta go"?

16:36.954 --> 16:37.871
It was just--

16:37.955 --> 16:40.457
Everybody is just go, go, go all the time.

16:40.916 --> 16:43.794
Then I found myself getting lost.
I didn't know who I was.

16:44.294 --> 16:47.006
I lost contact with family
for two years when I was there.

16:47.089 --> 16:48.799
-Really?
-Yeah, I was just--

16:48.882 --> 16:50.592
It was crazy. I was a mess. [laughs]

16:50.676 --> 16:53.095
I thought of it as trying to find myself.

16:53.512 --> 16:57.057
I kind of cut off anything
I had associated with home, away.

16:57.141 --> 17:00.936
Yeah. Has your mother--?
Has your relationship always been close?

17:01.311 --> 17:04.398
No. [laughs] When I first came out,
it was really hard.

17:04.481 --> 17:09.194
She came up on the small-town
Christian belief that you were condemned,

17:09.278 --> 17:12.656
and it was just disgusting,
and it's an abomination.

17:12.740 --> 17:15.367
-Yeah.
-She projected those feelings onto me.

17:15.784 --> 17:18.871
Which is hard, to the point
where I didn't like being around her.

17:18.954 --> 17:20.748
I didn't like being at home.

17:20.831 --> 17:24.001
But she got cancer my senior year
of high school.

17:24.084 --> 17:28.088
That gave her the time to really sit back
and reflect upon her life.

17:28.380 --> 17:31.759
How do you feel about this homecoming
your mother is putting together?

17:31.842 --> 17:32.718
I don't know.

17:32.801 --> 17:34.428
I'm a little iffy about it.

17:34.511 --> 17:38.348
[laughs] It's the fear I don't know
how they will receive me.

17:40.184 --> 17:45.481
I tell people all the time, you know,
this is a catchphrase people just use,

17:45.564 --> 17:49.318
and they let it roll off their tongue,
"What would Jesus do?"

17:49.401 --> 17:50.694
Right.

17:50.778 --> 17:55.783
You know? And I take that,
you know, very, very seriously.

17:55.866 --> 18:00.287
You can't antagonize and evangelize
at the same time, you know.

18:00.370 --> 18:03.749
And that's why the greatest commandment
of these is love.

18:03.832 --> 18:07.544
That's one of the things this homecoming
in the community center represents.

18:07.628 --> 18:09.797
Myles, come home.

18:10.339 --> 18:12.299
That's what we're gonna tell you.

18:13.133 --> 18:14.885
You're God's son.

18:15.636 --> 18:16.470
It's okay.

18:18.931 --> 18:22.518
-Oh! Before I start-- [laughs]
-Let's get out of here

18:22.601 --> 18:25.270
-and see how the other boys are doing.
-Oh, my God.

18:25.729 --> 18:26.688
Wow.

18:27.064 --> 18:28.941
-Hi.
-Hello.

18:29.024 --> 18:31.985
-We're just stooping it out here.
-Hi, sweetie.

18:32.778 --> 18:35.322
[Karamo] You are full of love and light.

18:36.031 --> 18:39.243
Seriously.
I just immediately felt at home.

18:39.326 --> 18:42.246
Yes, you're home. That's right.
Y'all are home.

18:42.329 --> 18:44.456
Normally, we have one person
we're gonna help,

18:44.540 --> 18:47.626
but the fact we're helping you,
which will serve your community,

18:47.709 --> 18:50.212
it's way better
than I could have expected.

18:50.295 --> 18:55.384
I'm expecting an incredible week of love

18:55.467 --> 19:00.722
and growth on everybody

19:00.806 --> 19:03.725
including myself,
and I'm looking forward to it.

19:03.809 --> 19:05.435
[Tan] It's gonna be amazing.

19:05.727 --> 19:07.312
-Yeah.
-It's gonna be so much fun.

19:07.396 --> 19:08.230
-Yeah.
-Yes.

19:08.313 --> 19:10.941
And you upped the population
of gay men in Gay, Georgia,

19:11.024 --> 19:13.026
-by 500 percent.
-I know.

19:13.110 --> 19:16.155
It is up by 500 percent.
You thought you're alone here?

19:16.238 --> 19:17.072
Okay?

19:17.156 --> 19:19.741
-Yes, time to open up a club.
-[all laughing]

19:19.825 --> 19:21.827
♪ I want you to stay ♪

19:24.204 --> 19:25.289
♪ In my life ♪

19:25.372 --> 19:26.540
♪ Lord ♪

19:26.915 --> 19:30.878
This homecoming in this community center
is a culmination of a lifetime of work.

19:30.961 --> 19:33.755
A lifetime of love.
It's also the culmination of a lifetime

19:33.839 --> 19:36.175
of Tammye not knowing
how to take care of herself.

19:36.258 --> 19:39.595
There is a diva in there. All she needs
is a bold lip and some lashes,

19:39.678 --> 19:43.056
and a new haircut,
so she can put her best foot forward.

19:44.266 --> 19:47.269
[Bobby] At first, it was hard for me
to wrap my head around a vision

19:47.352 --> 19:48.687
for the community center,

19:48.770 --> 19:53.483
because if you think about it,
this is literally 50 years in the making.

19:53.567 --> 19:57.946
A 50-year dream that's finally
being fulfilled by a bunch of gays.

19:58.030 --> 20:02.409
I mean, who'd have thought a bunch of gays
would come to Gay, Georgia,

20:02.492 --> 20:05.078
and build a community center for a church.

20:05.746 --> 20:08.290
[Antoni] It's especially rewarding
to help somebody

20:08.373 --> 20:10.709
who puts her own community before herself.

20:11.126 --> 20:13.712
I think we can learn from somebody
who's so grateful.

20:13.795 --> 20:18.675
I've been desperate for us
to finally take on a female as a client.

20:18.759 --> 20:20.844
She wanted to feel like a diva.

20:20.928 --> 20:25.307
I want Sundays, and in particular
this homecoming, for her to really shine.

20:26.558 --> 20:29.519
[Karamo] I'm hoping to encourage Myles
to be comfortable with himself.

20:29.603 --> 20:31.438
When he gets comfortable with himself,

20:31.521 --> 20:34.107
he'll realize that no matter where he is,
he belongs.

20:34.524 --> 20:40.030
♪ In my house ♪

20:53.502 --> 20:54.920
♪ Take my advice ♪

20:55.629 --> 20:58.090
♪ You better not be naughty
You'd better be nice ♪

20:58.173 --> 21:02.302
♪ Watch your P's and Q's
Everybody's gotta pay some dues ♪

21:02.386 --> 21:05.931
We're gonna prepare Mama's famous
banana pudding.

21:06.014 --> 21:07.933
-What's going on? Okay.
-Okay. [laughing]

21:10.477 --> 21:13.689
-[Tan] You know how this goes?
-I was making them before they were born.

21:13.772 --> 21:15.274
[Tan] Oh, you were? All right.

21:16.316 --> 21:19.403
We're gonna do a layer of crackers,
and then bananas.

21:19.486 --> 21:22.114
[Antoni] These wafers,
when they soak up the pudding,

21:22.197 --> 21:25.200
and they get all nice and soft, I mean...

21:25.284 --> 21:26.326
[laughs]

21:26.410 --> 21:28.370
We're gonna mix the milk.

21:28.453 --> 21:30.414
I used to say, "How much to put, Mama?"

21:30.497 --> 21:34.084
-She said, "Pour till I tell you to stop."
-Yes!

21:34.167 --> 21:35.502
-Do you all sing?
-I don't.

21:35.585 --> 21:36.545
I don't sing.

21:36.628 --> 21:38.380
-I don't.
-Not at all?

21:38.463 --> 21:41.049
The rest of the family, everybody--

21:41.133 --> 21:43.260
-Why don't you sing?
-We were robbed.

21:43.343 --> 21:45.137
[all laughing]

21:45.220 --> 21:47.389
I'm kind of like the wind
beneath the wings, like:

21:47.472 --> 21:49.099
[singing]

21:51.893 --> 21:53.145
Yes.

21:53.228 --> 21:55.897
As a matter of fact,
Myles was one of the ones

21:55.981 --> 21:58.025
that started the praise team at church.

21:58.108 --> 22:01.236
-He grew up singing in the choir.
-[Tan] Yeah.

22:01.320 --> 22:06.408
He recognized the voices, gathered them
together, and rehearsed with them and all.

22:06.491 --> 22:08.243
Then he went off to college.

22:08.327 --> 22:10.120
[Tan] Did he learn singing from you?

22:10.454 --> 22:13.415
Yeah, he did. When he was small.

22:13.498 --> 22:15.167
I always encouraged him.

22:15.250 --> 22:20.213
Even when he was in college,
he sang in the choir there. Wow.

22:20.297 --> 22:23.550
So, why is Myles hesitant to come back?
Do you know?

22:24.343 --> 22:29.514
He's just struggling that,
will he be accepted?

22:29.598 --> 22:33.769
It's just a matter of overcoming his fear,
because he has shared

22:33.852 --> 22:36.229
with me that he has been bullied.

22:36.313 --> 22:38.356
Hopefully, he can find a way to move on

22:38.440 --> 22:40.859
by seeing acceptance from you guys,
at least.

22:40.942 --> 22:44.029
Other kids who bullied him
may not ever accept him.

22:44.112 --> 22:46.907
May not ever change their hearts.
As long as you are open

22:46.990 --> 22:48.909
-and willing to accept him.
-Yes.

22:50.160 --> 22:52.412
[Tan] How was it when he first told you
he was gay?

22:52.496 --> 22:54.331
He told you when he was 14, right?

22:54.414 --> 22:58.585
Around 14. It took me aback for a minute,
and for a while,

22:58.668 --> 23:00.337
and it was a process.

23:00.420 --> 23:02.881
Brenda, she was the one that was always--

23:02.964 --> 23:06.134
You know, she will talk to me,
you know, about it.

23:06.218 --> 23:09.471
When God enlightened my heart,
we sat around this table.

23:09.554 --> 23:11.723
I sat here, he sat there.

23:12.224 --> 23:15.560
And I said, "Mama needs
to apologize to you."

23:15.811 --> 23:19.731
And he looked at me in my eyes,
and he was like, "For what, Mama?"

23:19.940 --> 23:25.445
I said, "Because Mama loves you.
You know that, right?"

23:25.821 --> 23:27.239
And he said, "Yes."

23:27.322 --> 23:30.325
I said, "But I need to ask you
for your forgiveness,

23:30.909 --> 23:34.412
because Mama has not loved you
unconditionally."

23:35.747 --> 23:39.126
And, you know, he looked at me, he's--

23:39.209 --> 23:41.837
"Mama, I forgave you a long time ago."

23:42.170 --> 23:45.715
And I said,
"No, I need to hear you say that."

23:46.424 --> 23:51.930
I said, because the Bible that I read
tells me that if I have wronged somebody,

23:52.013 --> 23:53.682
I mistreated someone,

23:54.266 --> 23:58.979
to ask their forgiveness first,
and then I'm free to go to the father.

23:59.062 --> 24:02.524
And I told him at that point,
"Your Mama has your back."

24:03.233 --> 24:06.278
[Antoni] She thought her faith told her
to judge somebody who's gay.

24:06.862 --> 24:09.739
But she chose to see past that,
and she saw the individual.

24:09.823 --> 24:13.076
She saw the person that her son is
and changed her mind.

24:13.535 --> 24:16.830
She says that it was a religious
experience, but she made that choice.

24:18.707 --> 24:20.125
Not all parents do that.

24:21.209 --> 24:23.879
One of the things for me, you know,

24:23.962 --> 24:27.424
that I struggled with
when Myles came out to me that he was gay,

24:27.507 --> 24:31.720
I think it felt like almost a broken dream

24:31.803 --> 24:34.431
of him having a child.

24:34.514 --> 24:35.557
I get that.

24:35.640 --> 24:40.103
-Do you mean that for Myles or for you?
-For me, you know.

24:40.187 --> 24:42.314
That dream of him having,

24:42.397 --> 24:46.109
you know, a natural child that's his,
you know what I'm saying?

24:46.193 --> 24:48.987
Myles can still have kids.
I'm working on my kids next year.

24:49.070 --> 24:50.906
-They're gonna be my children.
-Yes.

24:50.989 --> 24:53.325
We're gonna have a surrogate,
but they're my babies.

24:53.408 --> 24:55.994
Just because he's gay doesn't mean
he won't have children.

24:56.077 --> 24:58.496
-Yeah, oh, yeah.
-Yes!

25:06.004 --> 25:09.591
In the beginning, I was apprehensive
about this renovation.

25:09.674 --> 25:13.053
The Church was involved,
and I was worried we'd be judged

25:13.136 --> 25:16.932
and not accepted, but that's not
what I've gotten with Tammye.

25:17.015 --> 25:18.391
-Hey, looking good.
-Hey.

25:18.475 --> 25:20.393
-How you doing? Doing good?
-We're quick.

25:20.477 --> 25:21.770
Oh, yes, fantastic.

25:21.853 --> 25:25.482
I'm excited to be helping Miss Tammye
fulfill her and her mama

25:25.565 --> 25:29.444
and grandmama's dream
of making that community center a reality.

25:29.527 --> 25:33.531
I want to make it a space where kids have
their place, the elderly have their place.

25:33.615 --> 25:37.702
It's the perfect harmony of people
coming together to help each other.

25:40.038 --> 25:41.539
[pop music playing]

25:48.588 --> 25:52.968
We're gonna do a surprise.
Your mama doesn't know you're coming.

25:53.051 --> 25:56.388
Oh, my gosh. So, today
is Tammye's daughter's birthday.

25:56.471 --> 25:59.140
We need to have
a Steel Magnolias moment.

26:00.141 --> 26:02.269
-Look who we have.
-Hi.

26:02.894 --> 26:04.229
[Jonathan] Get over here.

26:04.562 --> 26:05.981
-Hi.
-[Jonathan] How are you?

26:06.064 --> 26:08.400
You look gorgeous in this yellow dress.

26:08.483 --> 26:10.026
-Thank you.
-I'm Jonathan.

26:10.110 --> 26:11.528
-I'm Brenda.
-Nice to meet you.

26:11.611 --> 26:14.823
Tammye's totally stuck
in a color rut with her hair.

26:14.906 --> 26:18.201
She doesn't know how to come out
and be the diva she was born to be.

26:18.285 --> 26:21.079
I'm like, "Just because you only
spend five minutes on glam

26:21.162 --> 26:22.872
does not mean you cannot be a diva."

26:22.956 --> 26:26.793
I want to tone this color down
closer to your natural color.

26:26.876 --> 26:29.296
Then I'm gonna take some of this color

26:29.379 --> 26:32.882
on the top that has some of the lightness,
and isolate that.

26:32.966 --> 26:36.011
It'll be more like a natural vibe,
like you went to Costa Rica,

26:36.094 --> 26:39.347
and you were surfing, you were celebrating
your cancer-free life,

26:39.431 --> 26:42.100
and you got a bit of a tan,
so you got a bit of tips.

26:42.183 --> 26:43.768
-There you go, honey.
-Yes.

26:43.852 --> 26:46.730
Doing block treatment for Jessica.
Tightening up her roots.

26:46.813 --> 26:50.066
And I have got my hands full
transforming Tammye.

26:50.150 --> 26:52.152
We're gonna have so much fun.

26:52.235 --> 26:55.071
♪ The way she moves
The way she shakes ♪

26:56.114 --> 27:00.452
Listen, when your mother's not around
she talks about you in a way that--

27:00.535 --> 27:03.663
Like, "Who's this Prince Charming
about to walk through this door?"

27:03.747 --> 27:05.790
-"Who's this?" You know?
-Yeah.

27:05.874 --> 27:10.253
Once you believe that more, other things
in your life will start changing.

27:10.337 --> 27:12.589
Like, picking up after yourself.

27:12.672 --> 27:13.715
[laughing]

27:13.798 --> 27:15.383
That's a big one.

27:16.509 --> 27:20.889
Part of, like, when you're not feeling
the best is also reflected in other areas.

27:20.972 --> 27:22.891
[Jonathan] Are you so excited
for the homecoming?

27:22.974 --> 27:24.225
I am, I am.

27:24.309 --> 27:26.603
How many people do you think
will come for that?

27:26.686 --> 27:28.521
At least 200, if not more.

27:28.605 --> 27:29.773
-Crap.
-Yes.

27:32.400 --> 27:35.278
Yes, Halle. I didn't know
I was gonna meet Halle Berry today.

27:35.362 --> 27:38.823
-Get away from here, boy. Get away.
-With this haircut. Get out of here.

27:38.907 --> 27:41.826
No. I won't. [laughing]

27:42.452 --> 27:44.829
Your mother invited you
to this homecoming.

27:44.913 --> 27:47.707
-Yeah.
-I understand your apprehension.

27:47.791 --> 27:50.001
I've had a different experience
with the Church.

27:50.085 --> 27:52.921
For me, anytime someone came
with their ignorance

27:53.004 --> 27:56.466
and tried to say like,
"You're going to hell," or whatever,

27:56.549 --> 27:59.177
I always was like,
"My granny taught me God is love.

27:59.260 --> 28:01.596
So, I'm not even listening
to what you're saying."

28:01.679 --> 28:03.973
I did feel the love
and everything, it was like--

28:04.057 --> 28:09.604
I just need to get over the fact
that it went down. [laughs] You know?

28:09.687 --> 28:11.648
-Is that a point of contention?
-Yeah.

28:11.731 --> 28:15.151
There's still that point where
you're thinking like, they don't love you.

28:15.235 --> 28:16.903
You know, even if they do.

28:16.986 --> 28:20.865
There's still that little voice
that's like, they're not for it.

28:20.949 --> 28:25.578
Truth be told, like, this homecoming
celebration is bigger than church.

28:25.662 --> 28:28.540
Because whether or not
you go back to church

28:28.623 --> 28:32.794
and start participating in organized
religion again is not the real thing here.

28:32.877 --> 28:34.504
-Exactly.
-Like, homecoming

28:34.587 --> 28:38.258
is for us to come around people
we love and be reenergized.

28:38.341 --> 28:40.510
-A big family reunion.
-A big family reunion.

28:40.593 --> 28:43.096
So, I just need to know, are you gonna go?

28:47.100 --> 28:48.435
-Yeah. Yeah.
-Okay.

28:48.518 --> 28:49.728
Anything for her. [laughs]

28:51.271 --> 28:53.898
♪ Just like the tides of the ocean ♪

28:55.775 --> 28:58.153
♪ Like a rocket in the sky
Come on ♪

28:58.236 --> 28:59.154
Hey, Mama.

28:59.237 --> 29:00.238
Hey.

29:00.321 --> 29:02.532
-Oh, my God. Mama.
-How are you?

29:02.615 --> 29:03.783
[Tammye] Give me some sugar.

29:04.909 --> 29:07.579
-You getting that pampering treatment?
-Yes.

29:07.662 --> 29:11.207
I brought him so he can get pampered, too.
He needs to get his hair cut.

29:11.291 --> 29:12.667
Come on. Come on.

29:13.084 --> 29:16.212
I love that Tammye is getting pampered,
but I wanna pamper Myles.

29:16.546 --> 29:19.674
We need to shape all of that up,
so you're just fresh.

29:19.758 --> 29:23.636
It's true. When you work on the outside,
sometimes it makes you feel better inside.

29:23.720 --> 29:25.138
A hug, baby girl.

29:26.848 --> 29:27.891
Hi.

29:30.185 --> 29:32.228
[Karamo] Look at that. You look great.

29:33.021 --> 29:35.315
-Oh, wow.
-[Karamo] Peter Gunz. Killed it.

29:36.816 --> 29:38.735
-That's nice.
-You look good.

29:39.402 --> 29:41.946
-Why are you shaking? Nervous? Why?
-A little bit.

29:42.030 --> 29:43.490
I don't know, it's a big thing.

29:43.573 --> 29:45.408
-Homecoming is me coming back.
-Yeah.

29:45.492 --> 29:48.661
It doesn't matter how they're gonna
take you, they're gonna see you.

29:48.745 --> 29:52.081
You're going there
to enjoy yourself with your family.

29:52.165 --> 29:54.125
Coming home, reconnect with them.

29:54.751 --> 29:58.213
[Jonathan] You highlight that cheekbone,
like, she's running away from you.

29:58.296 --> 30:00.131
-[Karamo] Stay next to me.
-Don't you wink at me

30:00.215 --> 30:02.967
-trying to make me feel certain things.
-Look at him.

30:03.051 --> 30:06.513
-Oh, Myles.
-I have something to tell you.

30:06.805 --> 30:11.518
Um, first of all, the clothes in my room,
