30:15.188 --> 30:16.898
until I'm down, that's what happens.

30:16.981 --> 30:20.985
So, I'm gonna work on motivating myself
to do better, you know?

30:21.069 --> 30:22.487
-Like--
-Oh, Myles.

30:22.570 --> 30:24.239
[Myles] And second of all...

30:25.031 --> 30:29.828
I've decided after a lot of thought
and consideration... to go to homecoming.

30:30.370 --> 30:31.663
[shouting]

30:31.746 --> 30:32.789
[all laughing]

30:33.164 --> 30:34.582
Jesus!

30:35.834 --> 30:37.377
Thank you, Jesus!

30:38.711 --> 30:39.587
Yes.

30:43.049 --> 30:45.927
-Yeah. I'm excited.
-Welcome home, Myles.

30:46.010 --> 30:49.347
I used to-- At him about going to church
or whatever.

30:49.430 --> 30:54.185
And my mom would always say,
"Leave him alone. He's gonna be okay."

30:54.269 --> 30:55.687
You know? And I just...

30:58.857 --> 31:03.862
[sobbing] I just wish she was here to see
that he's okay, you know?

31:04.487 --> 31:05.488
We're all okay.

31:06.072 --> 31:09.909
-I just-- I'm sorry, y'all. I just--
-[Karamo] No, do not apologize.

31:09.993 --> 31:13.621
-Give your mama a hug.
-Oh, my God, Myles.

31:14.247 --> 31:16.457
We have another surprise,
Bobby and I, for you.

31:16.541 --> 31:19.377
-So, we're gonna leave you back to this.
-Bye.

31:20.295 --> 31:21.462
Bye. Thank you.

31:21.546 --> 31:25.383
-Bye, everybody.
-So, I know that was a good moment.

31:25.466 --> 31:27.135
I love that you and Myles had that,

31:27.218 --> 31:29.721
but are you ready to fall in love
with your new hair?

31:29.804 --> 31:34.017
All right. We're happening. Ready?
Three, two, one, and here we are.

31:34.559 --> 31:35.476
Wow.

31:35.643 --> 31:37.312
Let me take this off of you.

31:37.395 --> 31:38.771
-Oh, my Lord.
-So you can see.

31:39.439 --> 31:42.108
Look at this hair.
She's like, "Get all up in that hair.

31:42.191 --> 31:43.651
Give yourself a gander."

31:44.110 --> 31:45.069
Wow.

31:45.695 --> 31:47.530
-Doesn't she look amazing?
-Oh, my Lord.

31:47.614 --> 31:49.324
-[Jonathan] The lightness to your ends.
-Yes.

31:49.407 --> 31:53.119
-Yes. Yes.
-But see how shiny and gorge?

31:54.037 --> 31:55.872
Oh, my goodness.

31:55.955 --> 31:57.248
Give me a hug.

31:57.332 --> 32:00.418
-I love you so much.
-I love you, love you, love you.

32:01.336 --> 32:03.004
[choir singing]

32:11.054 --> 32:12.555
-[Karamo] Do you hear them?
-Yes.

32:12.639 --> 32:16.267
Are you excited? You thought we were
joking we're bring the choir.

32:16.351 --> 32:18.227
[Myles] I didn't think you were joking.

32:18.645 --> 32:19.562
-You're home.
-Gosh.

32:20.063 --> 32:22.690
[Karamo] When you're struggling to fit in,
find the places

32:22.774 --> 32:25.526
where you feel like you belong.
They're not gonna find you.

32:25.610 --> 32:26.694
Are you nervous?

32:26.778 --> 32:28.780
No. I'm just excited.

32:41.960 --> 32:43.378
-Beautiful.
-Thank you.

32:43.461 --> 32:44.921
[all cheering]

32:45.004 --> 32:48.549
-Hey, Robert. How are you doing?
-[Robert] I'm great. How about you?

32:48.633 --> 32:50.301
-This is Myles.
-So nice to meet you.

32:50.385 --> 32:52.345
-[Bobby] That was beautiful.
-It was.

32:52.428 --> 32:54.639
It took me back to my choir days.

32:54.722 --> 32:56.474
Same here. [laughing]

32:56.557 --> 32:58.393
[Robert] Are you gonna audition for us?

32:58.476 --> 33:00.645
-[Karamo] You want us to audition? Sure.
-Yeah.

33:01.312 --> 33:03.314
So just-- Put him in the back.

33:04.691 --> 33:07.777
That's what they said about J.Lo,
and you see where she is.

33:07.860 --> 33:11.531
In my mind, I sound like
Luther Vandross when I'm singing.

33:11.614 --> 33:13.533
[sings, then clearing throat]

33:13.616 --> 33:15.868
[Robert] We're gonna sing
"The Battle of Jericho."

33:15.952 --> 33:17.078
Oh, so exciting.

33:17.161 --> 33:20.039
-Where do we sit?
-You're behind those curtains.

33:20.123 --> 33:21.582
[all laughing]

33:21.708 --> 33:26.421
John Legend, Michael Jackson.
I mean, like, that's how my range is.

33:26.504 --> 33:28.756
I like the back row. Y'all cute.

33:28.840 --> 33:31.592
-That's the troublemakers, so...
-I'm in the perfect spot.

33:31.676 --> 33:32.969
Perfect spot, then.

33:34.554 --> 33:36.222
Okay, pitches, please.

33:36.305 --> 33:38.266
-[Karamo] Can we stand?
-You can stand.

33:38.349 --> 33:40.143
Two, ready and go.

33:40.226 --> 33:43.104
♪ Joshua fit the battle
The battle of Jericho ♪

33:43.187 --> 33:46.190
♪ Joshua fit the battle
The battle of Jericho ♪

33:46.274 --> 33:48.526
♪ Joshua
The battle, Joshua ♪

33:48.609 --> 33:51.112
♪ Joshua fit the battle
The battle of Jericho ♪

33:51.696 --> 33:54.657
♪ Joshua fit the battle
The battle of Jericho ♪

33:54.741 --> 33:57.035
♪ Jericho ♪

33:57.326 --> 34:01.873
♪ The walls ♪

34:01.956 --> 34:08.963
♪ Come tumbling ♪

34:09.380 --> 34:16.387
♪ Down ♪

34:17.722 --> 34:18.890
That was fun.

34:18.973 --> 34:21.559
-So, how did Bobby do?
-[Timothy] He's got the notes.

34:21.642 --> 34:23.311
[Robert] He's got the notes. [laughs]

34:23.394 --> 34:24.687
That-- Hmm.

34:25.229 --> 34:27.899
Just like Myles, I quit singing years ago.

34:27.982 --> 34:30.610
But I was able to fill that void
with design--

34:30.693 --> 34:32.570
Myles, would you like to sing the solo,

34:32.653 --> 34:35.198
the beginning of "A Prayer"
for your audition?

34:35.281 --> 34:36.115
Definitely.

34:36.199 --> 34:38.201
--which helped me to move forward

34:38.284 --> 34:40.453
and not get into the funks
that you can get in

34:40.536 --> 34:42.997
when you aren't fulfilling the passions
in your life,

34:43.081 --> 34:45.041
like Myles when he stopped singing.

34:45.124 --> 34:50.797
♪ When I am dying, let me know ♪

34:52.173 --> 34:55.843
♪ That I loved the blowing snow ♪

34:56.177 --> 35:00.431
♪ Although it stung like whips ♪

35:00.681 --> 35:03.601
♪ Like whips ♪

35:03.684 --> 35:06.312
Oh, wasn't that beautiful, everybody?
Yeah.

35:06.395 --> 35:07.730
[all cheering]

35:10.983 --> 35:13.611
[Robert] So, we were going to make you
an honorary member,

35:13.694 --> 35:17.365
but I think it's so great that he ought
to just become a member. All right.

35:17.990 --> 35:22.745
-You're like, "Oh, he can sing."
-He can sing. So, you got a T-shirt.

35:22.829 --> 35:24.664
-Thank you so much.
-All right.

35:24.747 --> 35:27.834
-Okay. Welcome.
-Definitely. Thank you. Thank you.

35:29.335 --> 35:32.547
[Myles] I was raised on this for, like,
ten years, and I quit.

35:32.630 --> 35:35.341
It's like a piece of me is gone
because I stopped.

35:35.424 --> 35:38.678
This was my passion.
Like, this is what I was known for.

35:38.761 --> 35:41.472
There's people
with that story in this room.

35:41.556 --> 35:43.599
They'd love to share that story.

35:43.683 --> 35:47.061
-Thank you. We appreciate this.
-Thank you. Thank you for being here.

35:47.145 --> 35:49.897
-Bye, everyone. Thank you so much.
-Thank you.

35:49.981 --> 35:54.193
♪ Once in a while ♪

35:54.777 --> 35:57.196
♪ You'll speak to me ♪

36:02.493 --> 36:05.538
-Oh, my God.
-[laughs]

36:06.122 --> 36:08.166
How do you feel
now that your room is clean?

36:08.249 --> 36:11.210
Refreshed. It feels good.
Not heavy, like it did.

36:11.294 --> 36:15.381
Since you said you're coming tonight,
I actually got you an outfit.

36:15.464 --> 36:18.634
-So, you're excited?
-Yeah. [laughing]

36:23.598 --> 36:26.517
Hello-- Oh, look how gorge you look.

36:26.601 --> 36:27.435
Thank you.

36:27.518 --> 36:29.645
That jacket is all kinds of right.

36:29.729 --> 36:30.813
We're home.

36:30.897 --> 36:33.274
-Excited to see your place?
-Yes, I can't wait.

36:33.858 --> 36:35.818
-[Bobby] Oh, they're here.
-Oh, let's go.

36:35.902 --> 36:37.945
-Hey!
-Hey!

36:38.029 --> 36:41.324
-Are you y'all ready for Foxy Mama?
-[Fab 5] Yeah!

36:41.407 --> 36:42.867
Look at you.

36:42.950 --> 36:45.286
-You look gorgeous.
-Hey, fabulicious.

36:45.369 --> 36:47.163
You look so good.

36:47.246 --> 36:49.290
-Come on. Here we go.
-Come on in.

36:49.373 --> 36:50.208
Welcome home.

36:50.291 --> 36:51.375
-Go, go, go.
-After you.

36:51.459 --> 36:53.502
[Antoni]
I am stealing you first into the kitchen.

36:53.586 --> 36:56.088
Let's get some cooking for the homecoming.

36:56.172 --> 36:57.006
Yes.

36:57.089 --> 37:00.092
Usually, I'm the one teaching,
but I'm gonna give you the reins.

37:00.176 --> 37:02.470
-Teach me how to make your pasta salad.
-Oh, yes.

37:02.553 --> 37:06.557
I always put a dab of salt in here, so
that I don't have to add salt at the end.

37:06.641 --> 37:10.978
You want to concentrate on your eggs now.
Those just cook pretty quick.

37:11.062 --> 37:13.898
How many people are you expecting today?

37:13.981 --> 37:16.859
-At least 200.
-How are you gonna feed all these people?

37:16.943 --> 37:20.655
You'll see. Their hearts are full,
and their stomach is full.

37:20.738 --> 37:23.699
-Where there's a will, there's a way.
-I'm gonna work on the eggs.

37:23.783 --> 37:25.076
I'd love to know real quick,

37:25.159 --> 37:27.745
how many of the condiments
you're gonna be putting in?

37:27.828 --> 37:31.332
Mayo-- It's according
to how the macaroni soaks up.

37:31.415 --> 37:34.961
-We are not skimping on the mayonnaise.
-There you go. Exactly.

37:35.044 --> 37:36.504
[Antoni] And now how much relish?

37:36.587 --> 37:39.882
So maybe about half this jar. You wanna
put just a squeeze of mustard,

37:39.966 --> 37:43.344
because I like to put just enough
to give it a little color.

37:43.427 --> 37:46.138
-Beautiful.
-Wow, that's looking good, honey.

37:46.222 --> 37:48.182
-Why don't you try it?
-Are you feeding me?

37:48.266 --> 37:50.268
Yeah, I'm feeding you. One second.

37:51.227 --> 37:53.604
-What do you think?
-That's delicious.

37:53.688 --> 37:56.315
Bobby, come here. Give them a bite.

37:56.399 --> 38:00.486
Oh, it's so creamy, it's so creamy.
Just, like, a nice little texture.

38:00.778 --> 38:01.612
[Tammye] Yeah.

38:01.696 --> 38:05.116
-I could eat this whole thing.
-You know what, get ready.

38:05.199 --> 38:08.035
I know how to make more of this,
so I'm gonna keep making it.

38:08.119 --> 38:11.831
-Two hundred people.
-What? Oh, you got a lot of work to do.

38:11.914 --> 38:14.041
-I know.
-At least. At least.

38:14.500 --> 38:18.129
-You boys ready?
-Yeah. Come on in, Mama.

38:18.713 --> 38:21.507
Oh, my God.

38:22.466 --> 38:25.928
Is this the same place?
Is this the same boy?

38:26.012 --> 38:28.848
Oh, my God.

38:28.931 --> 38:30.474
Who transformed this room?

38:31.058 --> 38:32.101
I did. [laughs]

38:32.685 --> 38:34.478
[Karamo] Without any of us asking.

38:34.562 --> 38:37.565
Oh, Myles, oh!

38:37.982 --> 38:40.401
This is the young man I knew he could be.

38:40.484 --> 38:41.319
-Yes.
-Yeah.

38:41.402 --> 38:43.446
-Look at the shoes.
-[all laughing]

38:43.529 --> 38:47.199
-Just look at-- Oh, my God. Yes!
-Yes.

38:47.742 --> 38:50.828
Now you've seen how spiffy he looks,
we're gonna take you downstairs.

38:50.911 --> 38:52.455
We're gonna get you ready now.

38:52.538 --> 38:55.499
-Your turn, Mama.
-Get ready for your homecoming.

38:56.083 --> 38:57.043
Hi.

39:00.504 --> 39:03.049
[Bobby] I know you didn't want us
to do anything for you,

39:03.132 --> 39:05.426
but you deserve you time.

39:05.509 --> 39:09.847
And now you can come in here, take a
bubble bath, and take care of Tammye.

39:09.930 --> 39:11.140
[shouting]

39:13.517 --> 39:16.103
[Tammye] This is a dream. Wake me up.

39:16.645 --> 39:19.607
Mm, mm, mm! Mm, mm!

39:19.857 --> 39:21.734
My own space.

39:22.360 --> 39:24.987
What--? How did you do that?

39:25.571 --> 39:27.156
Miracles happen.

39:27.239 --> 39:29.784
[Tan] Will you come in with me?
I need her hair and makeup.

39:29.867 --> 39:32.495
You want a "diva" diva,
that's what he's gonna give you.

39:32.578 --> 39:34.997
-Yeah?
-[Tammye] Thank you. Thank you, sweetie.

39:35.081 --> 39:38.167
Tammye is a giver, but one thing
Tammye needs more than anything

39:38.250 --> 39:41.045
is one safe place
where she can give to herself.

39:41.128 --> 39:43.130
I'm just gonna polish that up.

39:43.214 --> 39:44.423
She deserves to fly.

39:45.174 --> 39:46.967
-[Tan] Okay, ladies, you ready?
-Yes.

39:48.177 --> 39:49.053
How do I look?

39:49.970 --> 39:51.013
Just kidding.

39:53.766 --> 39:55.434
-Yes.
-Classic.

39:55.518 --> 39:57.353
-Yeah.
-Oh, I love...

39:57.436 --> 39:59.230
-Yes.
-the texture up top.

39:59.605 --> 40:01.023
The little peek-a-boo.

40:01.565 --> 40:03.984
The women, they're gonna be so jealous.

40:04.068 --> 40:05.277
Yeah!

40:05.361 --> 40:07.071
-As they should be.
-Gorgeous.

40:07.154 --> 40:10.574
And the men, they gonna look like,
are we in church?

40:10.658 --> 40:13.536
Yes! Let's it take it there.

40:13.619 --> 40:16.122
-We should head over there.
-Time to go? Let's go!

40:16.205 --> 40:17.706
Okay. It's time to go.

40:17.790 --> 40:21.961
-Okay, get this stuff in the car.
-You guys can each grab one of those.

40:23.796 --> 40:26.841
I am so excited for homecoming.

40:27.758 --> 40:31.804
I knew how important your mother
and your grandmother were to you,

40:31.887 --> 40:34.890
and how this whole homecoming
was started from their legacy.

40:34.974 --> 40:37.435
-Yes.
-So, I wanted to get you a Bible

40:37.518 --> 40:41.397
that was inscribed with a Bible verse
and with their names.

40:44.400 --> 40:47.945
This is so powerful,
because my grandmother,

40:48.320 --> 40:50.156
she couldn't even read herself.

40:51.031 --> 40:53.284
But she's,
"I want y'all to know the Bible."

40:53.701 --> 40:57.413
Thinking back,
all the sacrifices that she made.

40:57.496 --> 40:59.623
-And then I look at my mom.
-Yeah.

40:59.707 --> 41:00.916
They always tell me,

41:01.000 --> 41:05.254
"Stay rooted and grounded
in the word of the Lord."

41:05.337 --> 41:06.547
[chuckles]

41:07.339 --> 41:10.384
So many people are gonna be
affected by this.

41:10.468 --> 41:12.595
So many. Oh, my gosh.

41:13.137 --> 41:14.096
You ready, Mama?

41:14.180 --> 41:17.224
-I'm taking my Bible to church.
-Yes, you are.

41:17.308 --> 41:19.977
-Let the church say amen.
-Amen.

41:20.060 --> 41:21.729
-Let's get out of here.
-Yes.

41:21.812 --> 41:25.191
-You ready to see the community center?
-Am I ready?

41:25.274 --> 41:28.569
-I've been waiting my whole life. Yes.
-Yeah.

41:39.663 --> 41:41.123
-Come on.
-Yeah.

41:42.625 --> 41:43.959
-[Bobby] You ready?
-[Tammye] Yes.

41:46.086 --> 41:47.379
[all] Yeah!

41:49.882 --> 41:51.258
Oh, jeez.

41:51.342 --> 41:53.427
-[Bobby] Are you ready?
-[Tammye] We're ready.

41:53.511 --> 41:54.887
[Bobby] All right, Miss Tammye.

41:56.305 --> 41:58.182
Oh, my...

41:58.766 --> 42:01.435
Oh, my...

42:02.228 --> 42:06.774
Oh, my God!

42:06.857 --> 42:10.194
♪ You lift me up and I am heaven ♪

42:11.737 --> 42:13.239
[Tammye] Look at this.

42:15.157 --> 42:19.537
This is beyond anything
that we could ever imagine.

42:19.620 --> 42:21.455
This is beautiful.

42:21.539 --> 42:23.415
[groaning, then chuckles]

42:26.502 --> 42:31.674
This has just been
through the efforts of so many people

42:31.757 --> 42:34.635
over the last 50-something years.

42:35.261 --> 42:39.765
Some are still here,
and some of them are gone.

42:39.848 --> 42:42.017
But this is their legacy.

42:43.519 --> 42:45.813
[Bobby] What do you think
your mama's thinking right now?

42:46.188 --> 42:49.984
-I feel like she is right here.
-Right here.

42:50.067 --> 42:51.193
Oh, my, yes.

42:52.653 --> 42:55.155
-[woman] She'll be so proud.
-Mm-hm.

42:56.907 --> 42:59.326
-Wow. Yes.
-Ready for some more? Okay.

42:59.410 --> 43:01.161
-Take a walk, look around.
-Thank you.

43:01.245 --> 43:02.496
[laughing]

43:02.580 --> 43:04.873
Everyone in the Town of Gay
could sit here.

43:04.957 --> 43:05.916
Yes.

43:06.834 --> 43:09.378
-And look over here.
-Little kids' area.

43:09.461 --> 43:12.089
-Yes!
-[Bobby] Little worktables to play.

43:12.172 --> 43:15.175
Areas for people to lounge,
and just fellowship.

43:15.259 --> 43:16.343
[Tammye] Yes.

43:17.094 --> 43:18.637
Couldn't have done it
without him.

43:18.721 --> 43:21.807
-Come here. Thank you, friend.
-I'm happy for you.

43:21.890 --> 43:25.477
Thank you. Oh, my God.
This place is incredible.

43:25.561 --> 43:29.607
And I think everyone involved
has grown and been touched this week.

43:29.690 --> 43:31.400
-I know I have.
-Us, too.

43:31.483 --> 43:33.944
[Tammye]
This has been a life-changing week for me.

43:34.028 --> 43:38.365
And, you know,
it's just God's amazing grace

43:38.449 --> 43:41.535
that we stand here
in this beautiful facility today.

43:41.702 --> 43:45.414
Before he gave the vision,
he already made provisions,

43:45.497 --> 43:48.250
'cause he knew you guys
would wind up together.

43:48.334 --> 43:52.296
Even before you were formed
in your mothers' wombs, he knew you.

43:52.379 --> 43:53.797
I just-- I'm thankful.

43:54.173 --> 43:58.093
Oh... Come here, Antoni. Antoni.

43:58.177 --> 43:59.553
[all laughing]

44:01.263 --> 44:02.973
Oh, my baby.

44:03.432 --> 44:05.684
You continue to let God use you, baby.

44:06.352 --> 44:09.897
Food is a way to the heart,
and more importantly, the soul.

44:10.272 --> 44:13.108
You keep feeding the souls
of people, okay?

44:13.484 --> 44:16.320
And you, Mister Glam.

44:17.112 --> 44:19.948
That's my new name.
You're calling me that from now on.

44:20.324 --> 44:24.953
Beauty. That's your calling in life.
Everything is made beautiful in its time.

44:25.496 --> 44:27.665
And you add beauty to the world.

44:27.748 --> 44:29.708
-It's your gift, okay?
-Thank you.

44:29.792 --> 44:33.170
You represent a lot of little boys
who look like you.

44:33.962 --> 44:38.384
And they wanna be like you, okay?
Continue making this world a better place.

44:40.010 --> 44:42.846
[Antoni] It's just, like,
one after the other. I can't.

44:44.014 --> 44:47.851
Where's my other babies back here?
Bobby, what have you learned this week?

44:48.268 --> 44:50.854
To remember where I came from.

44:50.938 --> 44:51.772
Yes.

44:51.855 --> 44:54.942
You know, and to let go
of some of the resentment.

44:55.025 --> 44:58.070
-Yes.
-And realize that not everyone out there

44:58.153 --> 45:00.447
that claims to be Christian is good.

45:00.531 --> 45:05.327
-But there are a lot out there that are.
-Yes, baby, more out there who are good.

45:06.453 --> 45:07.538
Come here, baby.

45:07.788 --> 45:09.164
[all laughing]

45:09.915 --> 45:12.459
This is the one I have to spank,
right here.

45:12.835 --> 45:14.962
-Get him.
-That's right.

45:15.045 --> 45:15.921
[all laughing]

45:16.964 --> 45:19.133
Your spirit is so, so pure.

45:19.508 --> 45:22.511
And all you guys, the gifts that you have,

45:22.594 --> 45:27.516
you're using it for the good of humanity,
and that's why you're here on this Earth.

45:27.891 --> 45:32.020
I feel like I have turned into a mirror,
because you're talking about yourself.

45:32.604 --> 45:35.315
You help everyone.
You make the world a better place.

45:35.399 --> 45:38.026
You're empowering your spirit
to everyone you touch.

45:38.569 --> 45:41.989
Tell your mother what you told me
when I asked why you were so quiet.

45:42.239 --> 45:45.242
I'm still nervous about going in.

45:46.827 --> 45:48.954
[Karamo] You have acknowledged
what you were feeling,

45:49.037 --> 45:52.040
and you have started making
dramatic changes for yourself.

45:52.124 --> 45:55.836
Now that you've showed up here,
God is doing the rest right now.

45:55.919 --> 45:59.798
This church and community,
they've opened their doors to us.

46:00.048 --> 46:03.635
Why wouldn't they to you, to someone
they've known and loved your whole life?

46:03.719 --> 46:05.137
Yes. Mm-hm.

46:05.721 --> 46:07.973
Mama's gonna be right there with you.

46:09.600 --> 46:11.101
Praise the Lord.

46:11.602 --> 46:14.229
-You're my children. I'll miss y'all.
-[Jonathan] Group hug.

46:14.313 --> 46:15.397
I'll miss y'all.

46:16.231 --> 46:17.649
I'm gonna miss y'all.

46:18.901 --> 46:20.027
Y'all make Mama proud.

46:20.110 --> 46:22.029
-I love all of y'all.
-We love you, too.

46:22.112 --> 46:26.033
♪ Amazing ♪

46:29.453 --> 46:31.914
♪ Grace ♪

46:32.581 --> 46:38.921
♪ How sweet ♪

46:39.463 --> 46:44.635
♪ The sound ♪

46:45.552 --> 46:48.972
The Church has not always
been accepting of the LGBT community,

46:49.056 --> 46:53.143
but this is what I've always seen.
The church is where we support each other

46:53.227 --> 46:55.103
to recharge, to rebuild.

46:55.187 --> 47:00.526
♪ Amazing ♪

47:03.779 --> 47:07.741
♪ Grace ♪

47:08.158 --> 47:14.289
♪ How sweet ♪

47:14.831 --> 47:19.753
♪ The sound ♪

47:20.796 --> 47:23.131
This is what I've always known
church to be.

47:23.215 --> 47:25.425
This love that Mama Tammye radiates.

47:27.844 --> 47:32.849
We thank God for the occasion we're
here on today, homecoming service.

47:33.100 --> 47:34.184
Yeah.

47:35.269 --> 47:37.813
-[man] Let us eat and be merry.
-[woman] Amen.

47:37.896 --> 47:39.064
[man] We just thank the Lord.

47:39.481 --> 47:41.817
If they ended up in Meriwether County

47:41.900 --> 47:44.278
with all these rural roads
and woods we have,

47:44.361 --> 47:46.613
they got to know God sent them down here.

47:46.697 --> 47:48.198
-[all] Yeah!
-Come on up.

47:48.907 --> 47:50.784
-Amen.
-Amen.

47:51.535 --> 47:53.078
[Tammye] I thank God for this week.

47:53.662 --> 47:56.748
This week, we worked with the Fab 5.

47:56.832 --> 48:00.043
They put their whole heart
into the community center.

48:00.961 --> 48:05.007
These are five gifted men who are gay.

48:05.757 --> 48:07.634
And through the course of the week,

48:07.718 --> 48:10.887
you know, we were able to build
some relationships.

48:10.971 --> 48:14.182
That's what it's about,
building relationships.

48:15.559 --> 48:21.690
They shared with me how they have been
just torn down and rejected.

48:23.025 --> 48:26.194
And the Church has turned their backs
on them.

48:26.987 --> 48:29.406
How can I say that I love God,

48:30.198 --> 48:34.536
but I cannot love the ones
who are right there next to me?

48:35.954 --> 48:37.873
I would call myself a hypocrite.

48:38.832 --> 48:43.962
And I say I was around five gay men,
I was around six.

48:45.922 --> 48:48.091
My son walked away from the Church,

48:48.175 --> 48:52.804
you know, and it's been my prayer
that he comes here and feel the love.

48:53.388 --> 48:57.559
You know, the love that Pastor Favors
founded this place on.

48:58.310 --> 49:01.396
The love that surrounds me every Sunday.

49:01.480 --> 49:04.358
Do I love Jesus? Yes.

49:04.441 --> 49:06.985
Am I a believer? Yes.

49:07.819 --> 49:10.656
Do I love my son? Yes.

49:11.865 --> 49:14.951
Yes, yes, yes.

49:15.494 --> 49:19.289
Mama Tammye is the epitome
of what Southern hospitality is about.

49:20.248 --> 49:22.626
-See.
-Come in, see what you got here.

49:22.709 --> 49:25.712
Mama has taught me so much
about unconditional love.

49:25.796 --> 49:27.339
Look at that, right there.

49:28.256 --> 49:32.594
[laughing] This is Myles,
my son I was talking about, right here.

49:32.678 --> 49:34.805
[Tan] She loves her son implicitly.

49:34.888 --> 49:38.934
Every parent who has a child
should love them no matter what.

49:39.017 --> 49:41.478
See right there?
See the picture of Pastor Favors?

49:42.145 --> 49:44.981
[Jonathan] At the end of the day,
if you're gay, straight, black, white,

49:45.065 --> 49:46.566
it doesn't matter who you are.

49:46.650 --> 49:48.735
We truly are all people
wanting to connect.

49:48.819 --> 49:49.820
Hey, girl.

49:50.237 --> 49:52.489
Before you go judge somebody,
get to know them.

49:52.572 --> 49:55.701
I guarantee you'll find you have
more similarities than differences.

49:55.784 --> 49:59.413
And that's what we all need to do
to everyone.

49:59.496 --> 50:00.956
Not just the LGBT community,

50:01.039 --> 50:03.375
but Christians, Muslims,
Hindus, Buddhists.

50:03.458 --> 50:07.921
Just love and accept them,
because that is what Jesus would do.

50:09.047 --> 50:11.091
